SELECT beer,bar
FROM Serves
EXCEPT
(
  SELECT Serves.beer, Serves.bar
  FROM
  Serves

  WHERE
  Serves.bar != s1.bar
);

/*Find all (beer, bar) pairs where beer is served exclusively at bar; no other bar serves the same beer*/

(SELECT DISTINCT A.beer, A.bar
FROM Serves A, Serves B
WHERE A.beer = B.beer)
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT A.beer, A.bar
FROM Serves A, Serves B
WHERE A.beer = B.beer
AND A.bar <> b.bar);

WITH UNIBEERS(beer) AS
(
  SELECT serves.beer
  FROM serves
  EXCEPT
  SELECT T.beer1
  FROM
  (
    SELECT serves1.bar AS bar1, serves2.bar AS bar2, serves1.beer AS beer1, serves2.beer AS beer2
    FROM serves AS serves1, serves AS serves2
    WHERE serves1.bar<>serves2.bar AND serves1.beer = serves2.beer
  ) T
)
SELECT FINAL.beer, FINAL.bar
FROM
  (
  SELECT serves.beer, serves.bar
  FROM UNIBEERS, serves
  WHERE UNIBEERS.beer=serves.beer
  ) FINAL;

FROM Serves AS s1

EXCEPT

FROM Serves AS s2
WHERE s2.beer IN (
    SELECT s3.beer
    FROM Serves AS s3
    WHERE s2.beer=s3.beer
    AND s2.bar != s3.bar
);

FROM serves
EXCEPT

WHERE s1.beer = s2.beer
AND NOT s1.bar = s2.bar;

column1:
SELECT serves.beer, bar
FROM serves,
       (SELECT beer
        FROM serves
        EXCEPT (SELECT DISTINCT s3.beer
                FROM (SELECT s1.beer
                        FROM serves AS s1,
                        serves AS s2
                        WHERE ((s1.beer = s2.beer) AND (s1.bar != s2.bar))) AS s3)) AS s4
        WHERE (serves.beer = s4.beer);

WITH TMP1(beer) AS
(SELECT DISTINCT pair1.beer
FROM serves AS pair1, serves AS pair2
WHERE pair1.bar != pair2.bar AND pair1.beer=pair2.beer)

SELECT DISTINCT serves.beer, serves.bar
FROM SERVES
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT serves.beer, serves.bar
FROM TMP1, serves
WHERE TMP1.beer=serves.beer);

	(SELECT  bar, beer FROM serves)
SELECT serves.beer, serves.bar
FROM serves
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT * 
	FROM pairs1
	WHERE serves.beer=pairs1.beer 
		AND serves.bar<>pairs1.bar);

column1:
SELECT beer, bar FROM Serves WHERE beer IN
(SELECT DISTINCT beer FROM Serves
EXCEPT SELECT DISTINCT s.beer
FROM Serves s, Serves r
WHERE s.beer = r.beer AND s.bar <> r.bar);

(SELECT beer, bar
FROM serves)

EXCEPT

(SELECT T1.beer, T1.bar
FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM serves) AS T1,
	 (SELECT bar, beer FROM serves) AS T2
WHERE T1.bar <> T2.bar and T1.beer = T2.beer);

/* Find all (beer, bar) pairs where beer is served exclusively at bar. */

SELECT beer, bar
FROM serves
EXCEPT
(
    SELECT s1.beer, s1.bar
    FROM serves AS s1
    CROSS JOIN serves AS s2
    WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar
    AND s1.beer = s2.beer
);

column1:
(SELECT beer, bar FROM serves)
EXCEPT
(SELECT beer1 AS beer, bar1 AS bar FROM (SELECT a.beer AS beer1, a.bar AS bar1 FROM serves AS a) AS a, (SELECT b.beer AS beer2, b.bar AS bar2 FROM serves AS b) AS b WHERE a.bar1<>b.bar2 AND a.beer1=b.beer2);

/*

First set of {beer, bar} pairs called 'a':
(SELECT a.beer AS beer1, a.bar AS bar1 FROM serves AS a)

Second set of {beer, bar} pairs called 'b':
(SELECT b.beer AS beer2, b.bar AS bar2 FROM serves AS b)

{beer, bar} where the bars are different but the drinks served are also served at another bar
(SELECT beer1 AS beer, bar1 AS bar FROM (SELECT a.beer AS beer1, a.bar AS bar1 FROM serves AS a) AS a, (SELECT b.beer AS beer2, b.bar AS bar2 FROM serves AS b) AS b WHERE a.bar1<>b.bar2 AND a.beer1=b.beer2)
*/

column1:
(SELECT beer, bar FROM Serves)
EXCEPT
(SELECT Serves2.beer, Serves2.bar
FROM  Serves Serves1
JOIN Serves Serves2 ON Serves1.beer = Serves2.beer 
		AND Serves1.bar<>Serves2.bar)

column1:
-- Find all (beer, bar) pairs where beer is served exclusively at bar; no other bar serves the same beer.

(select beer, bar from serves)
except
(select beer, bar
from serves as s1
where exists (select beer, bar from serves
              where beer=s1.beer and bar<>s1.bar));

column1:
(SELECT beer, bar
FROM serves)
EXCEPT ALL 
(SELECT beer, bar
FROM serves AS s
WHERE EXISTS (SELECT beer, bar
FROM serves
WHERE beer = s.beer 
AND bar <> s.bar));

column1:
-- Find all (beer,bar) pairs where beer is served exclusively at bar.
-- No other bar serves the same beer.
SELECT beer, bar 
FROM serves 
WHERE beer IN 
(
SELECT beer
FROM serves 
GROUP BY beer 
HAVING COUNT(*)=1

/*Find all (beer, bar) pairs where beer is served exclusively at bar; no other bar serves the same beer

#all combos EXCEPT any pairs of bars that serve the same beers*/
SELECT s3.beer, s3.bar FROM (SELECT s1.beer
	FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
EXCEPT
SELECT s1.beer
	FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.beer = s2.beer
	WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar) as s1
INNER JOIN serves s3 ON s1.beer = s3.beer;

column1:
SELECT beer, bar
FROM Serves
WHERE beer In
(SELECT beer
FROM Serves
WHERE beer NOT IN
(SELECT DISTINCT serves1.beer
FROM Serves serves1, Serves serves2
WHERE (serves1.beer = serves2.beer) AND (serves1.bar <> serves2.bar
))
);

FinalBeers.beer,
bar
FROM
(SELECT
beer
FROM
(SELECT
beer,
COUNT(*) AS amount
FROM
Serves
GROUP BY
beer) as BeerCount
WHERE
amount = 1 ) FinalBeers
JOIN
Serves on FinalBeers.beer = Serves.beer
;

WITH UNIQUES(beer) AS
(SELECT serves.beer
  FROM serves EXCEPT
SELECT T.beer1 FROM
  (SELECT serves1.bar AS bar1, serves2.bar AS bar2, serves1.beer AS beer1, serves2.beer AS beer2
    FROM serves AS serves1, serves AS serves2
    WHERE serves1.bar<>serves2.bar AND serves1.beer = serves2.beer) T)
SELECT FINAL.beer, FINAL.bar FROM
  (SELECT serves.beer, serves.bar
  FROM UNIQUES, serves
  WHERE UNIQUES.beer=serves.beer) FINAL;
